"""
ACCV Comparison: Signal Recovery (raw) vs Red Pitaya (cycle-averaged)

SR data is NEVER modified — plotted exactly as loaded.
RP gets full cycle-averaging treatment (up/down split, bin-avg, cycle-avg + sigma).

Layout: 2 columns x 3 rows
  Col 1: R plots
  Col 2: Theta plots

Row 1: vs Time          — SR raw line  +  RP raw line (auto-scaled)
Row 2: vs DC (scatter)  — SR raw scatter  +  RP bin-averaged scatter (up/down)
Row 3: vs DC (averaged) — SR raw scatter  +  RP cycle-averaged line  +/-1 sigma

SR files: signal.csv, phase.csv, time.csv, dcRamp.csv
RP file:  combined_results_*.csv
"""

